I need to design a new fictional "PulseBoard" channel plugin for the OpenClaw repo. PulseBoard is an imaginary real-time bulletin board messaging platform where users post messages to named "boards" and can also send direct messages. It should support both direct and group chat types, with a 4000-character text chunk limit.

CONSTRAINTS:
- Do NOT modify any existing files. Only create new files in `extensions/pulseboard/`.
- Follow the exact same extension structure as IRC (the reference plugin).
- Import only from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` (the public SDK surface).
- The plugin is fictional — no real API client is needed, but stub the send/monitor/probe functions realistically.

## Reference Plugin Structure (IRC)

The IRC plugin lives at `extensions/irc/` with these files:

### Top-level files:
- `package.json` — npm package with `openclaw` metadata block defining channel id, label, blurb, etc.
- `openclaw.plugin.json` — Plugin manifest with id, channels array, empty configSchema
- `index.ts` — Main entry via `defineChannelPluginEntry` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`
- `setup-entry.ts` — Lightweight setup entry via `defineSetupPluginEntry`
- `api.ts` — Public API barrel exports

### src/ files:
- `src/channel.ts` — Main plugin built with `createChatChannelPlugin()`. Defines capabilities, config adapter, groups, messaging, directory, status, gateway, pairing, security, and outbound.
- `src/runtime.ts` — Runtime store via `createPluginRuntimeStore`
- `src/runtime-api.ts` — Re-exports from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/irc` (SDK barrel for IRC)
- `src/types.ts` — TypeScript types: account config, core config, inbound message, probe result
- `src/config-schema.ts` — Zod schemas for config validation using `buildChannelConfigSchema`, `DmPolicySchema`, `GroupPolicySchema`, `MarkdownConfigSchema`, etc.
- `src/config-ui-hints.ts` — UI hints for config fields
- `src/accounts.ts` — Account resolution using `createAccountListHelpers`, `resolveMergedAccountConfig`, env var fallbacks, secret resolution
- `src/setup-core.ts` — Setup adapter with `ChannelSetupAdapter` interface
- `src/setup-surface.ts` — Setup wizard with `ChannelSetupWizard` — prompts for config values
- `src/normalize.ts` — Target/allowlist normalization
- `src/policy.ts` — Group access, require-mention, sender-allowed policies
- `src/send.ts` — Outbound message sending (stub for PulseBoard)
- `src/probe.ts` — Status probe (stub for PulseBoard)
- `src/monitor.ts` — Inbound monitor/connection (stub for PulseBoard)
- `src/inbound.ts` — Inbound message handling

